  "prompt": "Do snakes really take revenge?",
  "response": "No, snakes do not take revenge. Snakes are not capable of complex emotions like vengeance. They are driven by instinct and survival behaviors such as hunting, feeding, and avoiding threats. If a snake acts aggressively, it is usually because it feels threatened or cornered, not because it is seeking revenge for a past event. \n\nFor example, if a snake is handled roughly or perceives a human as a threat, it might bite in self-defense. This is a reflexive action, not a deliberate act of revenge. Understanding snake behavior and treating them with caution and respect can help avoid such situations.",
